    "created_at": "2018-09-02T02:35:28Z",
    "updated_at": "2018-09-02T02:35:28Z",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Just wanted to chime in that this seems to be the main performance bottleneck for me when reading in string index columns from Parquet (using, e.g., pyarrow).\r\n\r\nBecause they're dictionary-encoded on disk, they're efficiently read in as Categorical columns; calling set_index on this single column (to make a CategoricalIndex) or set_index with a string column and a few integer columns (to make a MultiIndex) takes 1-2min for 250M rows, which is longer than it actually takes to read the data from disk."
